―Baghera Jones

Baghera Jones is a Swiss and French-Speaking member of the QSMP[2], who was announced on May 11, 2023, and joined on May 16, 2023.[3]

She is portrayed by the content creator of the same name.

Personality[]

Baghera is easily distracted, and can be very energetic at times. While she may not be the most comfortable around people she doesn't know too well, she is very sensitive, compassionate, friendly, and easily chats with people. She does however have a mischievous side, stealing a bit here and there, playing pranks and making fun of herself and others.

Baghera prefers to focus on investigation, construction and creation rather than engaging in combat. She is highly intelligent and observant, and her theories often prove to be true. She is close to BadBoyHalo, and also gets on very well with all the French members. She is the one spending the most time taking care the French egg, Pomme, and she deeply worries about her. Since she doesn't want her own fears to end up making Pomme overly cautious, she lets Etoiles teach her fighting skills. But if something bad were to happen to her, Baghera would certainly do everything in her power to get revenge.

During Purgatory, she became insane and deranged, wanting nothing more then to kill. her iconic weapon became a chainsaw, which breaks armor down at a rapid rate. She mained it during the Egg Wars, as well as in Purgatory 2. In both Purgatories, she lost her sanity, constantly moving like a killing machine, desiring blood. She, however, was likely the calmest of Team Bolas, and occasionally felt as if she was spoken over a lot throughout her time. Nonetheless, Bolas is a key part of her, her considering it almost like an insane family.

After Purgatory, Baghera seems to have become like another person, while still retaining some of her past self (Pre-Purgatory). She is co-dependent on Philza, wanting to live with him and be by his side as his child. However, she is also very sensitive, feeling rejected by him often. She, however, still cares for her kids throughout, and also seems to hold no grudges from Purgatory. She still has reminiscence of her old personality.

Physiology[]

Baghera is a charming character who takes the form of a humanoid yellow duckling adorned with a distinctive propeller hat, which was later replaced with pink-purple hair. This hat stands out with its vibrant colors, featuring a captivating combination of four different hues. After having a scan, Baghera found out that she is 99% duck and 1% goldfish with gills underneath her wings. This discovery explains her short memory. However, she does not have all the features of a goldfish as she is only 1% goldfish. Baghera is always being followed around by little fireflies (her chat).

She has had many different versions of herself, skins fitting events and entirely new versions for character arcs.

Trivia[]

Character[]

Before the events of the Prison, she and Jaiden were the only women on the server. Both of them have promised to stand by each other on the day Baghera arrived. (Day 56)

She is an experiment of the Federation.

She refers to her Extendo-Grip as her 'Fuck Machine'.

Content Creator[]

She is half Spanish, understands some of the language and can speak it a little.

She made a song with Antoine called La vériter, as part of the ZZCCMXTP, a mixtape created by French musicians Kronomuzik, Ronare and Pandrezz grouping songs made by various French rappers, YouTubers and streamers. They performed it together at the Olympia in Paris on November 4th, 2022.[4]

She's part of "La team du lundi" with Antoine, Etoiles, Horty and Mynthos, a group that streams together on most Mondays. It's with this group of friends that she took part in her first SMP.

Baghera took part in the 2019 and 2022 editions of the ZEvent (each French member on the server took part at least twice). It's an annual charity event created by Zerator (one of France's biggest streamers) : for 3 days, French-speaking streamers all stream from the same location and collect donations for charity. With €10.1 million raised in 2022 for environmental associations, Zevent holds the world record for the highest-grossing charity event on Twitch.

She was involved with her friend Horty in RPZ, a two-week RP event organised by Zerator on Grand Theft Auto V in 2021. They were playing as cousins Antoine and Daniel Croute (a pun on Antoine Daniel's name, and at the end his character has adopted them), and they're among the most popular characters of the event. The last episode of their adventures is a film that they screened in a Paris cinema with an audience and simultaneously streamed on Twitch.

Like all the French team (except Aypierre), she took part in the 2022 Pixel War on Reddit alongside Kameto to fight against the American and Spanish communities, and helped France make its mark on the event.

Baghera took part in the second edition of the GP Explorer in a team with her friend Horty and sponsored by Cupra. It's a Formula 4 race organised by Squeezie (France's biggest youtuber and streamer) in which French-speaking internet personalities compete on the legendary Le Mans circuit. The first edition attracted over a million viewers on Twitch. After months of training, she faced the 11 other teams on September 9, 2023.
